We were walking on Wattamolla beach this afternoon, and saw 4 dead cormorants washed off on the beach. :( 
Any idea what might be going on? I have sent the picture to NSW National parks, but is there another place I should report this?
poor guy washed up

Five muttonbirds washed up on the beach all within a few metres of one another. Three are pictured. They are at the end of the beach that is bordered by the breakwall so might have been deposited here because they couldn't be washed any further along. They are at the high water mark on the sand and seem like they haven't been there long. They have a very slight smell to them but nothing overwhelming yet. They don't look to have been scavenged at all. They're all a similar size and were probably part of the mass die-off of the migrating group recently. Came across them at night after a hot and muggy day.
On high tide mark.
several of these washed up

Underparts are lighter coloured, though this seems a less reliable characteristic.
